{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-ac83815e8f222df4", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# Qwen2.5-Omni Technical Report\narXiv: 2503.20215\nAuthors: Jin Xu, Zhifang Guo, Jinzheng He, Hangrui Hu, Ting He, Shuai Bai, Keqin Chen, Jialin Wang, Yang Fan, Kai Dang, Bin Zhang, Xiong Wang, Yunfei Chu, Junyang Lin\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce Qwen2.5-Omni, a unified end-to-end multimodal model that perceives text, images, audio, and video while simultaneously generating streaming text and speech responses.\n  2. We propose TMRoPE, a novel positional embedding algorithm that explicitly incorporates temporal information to synchronize audio and video inputs.\n  3. We present the Thinker-Talker architecture, which enables concurrent text and streaming speech generation while minimizing interference between the two modalities.\n  4. We design block-wise processing for multimodal encoders and a sliding-window DiT mechanism to support efficient streaming inference and reduce initial packet delay.\n  5. We demonstrate that Qwen2.5-Omni achieves state-of-the-art performance on multimodal benchmarks, matches text-level intelligence with speech instructions, and generates highly robust and natural streaming speech.\n\nTags: LALM, TTS, LALM/对话型, TTS/功能-流式", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "5e26e7a0-0f45-4373-822e-3119a354126e", "uuid": "4485a431-2076-4049-a980-4d6a3b7d9b95", "timestamp": "2026-07-23T06:55:45.073Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# Qwen2.5-Omni Technical Report\narXiv: 2503.20215\nAuthors: Jin Xu, Zhifang Guo, Jinzheng He, Hangrui Hu, Ting He, Shuai Bai, Keqin Chen, Jialin Wang, Yang Fan, Kai Dang, Bin Zhang, Xiong Wang, Yunfei Chu, Junyang Lin\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce Qwen2.5-Omni, a unified end-to-end multimodal model that perceives text, images, audio, and video while simultaneously generating streaming text and speech responses.\n  2. We propose TMRoPE, a novel positional embedding algorithm that explicitly incorporates temporal information to synchronize audio and video inputs.\n  3. We present the Thinker-Talker architecture, which enables concurrent text and streaming speech generation while minimizing interference between the two modalities.\n  4. We design block-wise processing for multimodal encoders and a sliding-window DiT mechanism to support efficient streaming inference and reduce initial packet delay.\n  5. We demonstrate that Qwen2.5-Omni achieves state-of-the-art performance on multimodal benchmarks, matches text-level intelligence with speech instructions, and generates highly robust and natural streaming speech.\n\nTags: LALM, TTS, LALM/对话型, TTS/功能-流式", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
